<h1>
Debian GNU/NetBSD
</h1>

<p>
Debian GNU/NetBSD is a port of the Debian Operating System to the
NetBSD kernel. It is currently in an early stage of development and
cannot currently be installed from scratch. Instead, a tarball of the
current environment is available and can be extracted into a directory
on a NetBSD system.
</p>

<p>
<a href="http://www.srcf.ucam.org/~mjg59/debian-netbsd/debian-netbsd.tar.gz">
Download the current version of the Debian GNU/NetBSD system</a> (last
updated 14 January 2002)
</p>

<p>
<a href="why">Why Debian GNU/NetBSD?</a>
</p>

<h2>
Usage instructions
</h2>

<ul>
<li>Download the file</li>
<li>
Extract it somewhere. <strong>WARNING</strong> - do not extract this
in <kbd>/</kbd> - you will render your system unbootable
</li>
<li>
As root, <kbd>chroot /debian /bin/bash</kbd> (replace
<kbd>/debian</kbd> with wherever you've extracted the tarball)
</li>
<li>Play. Enjoy. Fix stuff.</li>
</ul>

